== Rice ==

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince @garlic{2%cloves}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add half the minced garlic and half the @turmeric{1%tsp} (all the turmeric for 4
servings). Cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups
for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low
simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chimichurri ==

While rice cooks, mince @parsley{1/4%oz}. Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%oz}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz}; cut crosswise into
1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(halved and
thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, pistachios, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@olive oil{2 1/2%tbsp}, @red wine vinegar{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (5 TBSP
olive oil and 2 tsp vinegar for 4).

> TIP: Add a little more vinegar if you prefer a tangier chimichurri.

== Turkey ==

Open package of @ground turkey{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a
drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add turkey;
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out
pan.

== Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
asparagus and sliced onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring,
until lightly browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

In the last minute of cooking, stir in @peas{4%oz} and remaining minced garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until garlic is fragrant and peas are warmed
through.

Use pan used for turkey here. Once peas are warmed through, stir turkey into
pan.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @golden raisins{}.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with veggies. Drizzle chimichurri
over top. Serve.